"title": "5699: guests",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5699: guests",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>People who receive hospitality, especially at others' homes. Guests are often invited to special celebrations such as weddings or birthdays. God invites all people as guests at his feast but many refuse.</p>\n<h2>Occasions for inviting guests</h2>\n<h3>Weddings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:21-Gen29:22\">GEN 29:21–29:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth2:17-Esth2:18\">EST 2:17–2:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:1-John2:10\">JHN 2:1–2:10</a></p>\n<h3>Birthday celebrations</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen40:20\">GEN 40:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:6\">MAT 14:6</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:21-Mark6:22\">MRK 6:21–6:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt14:9\">MAT 14:9</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:26\">MRK 6:26</a></p>\n<h3>Other special occasions</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam9:22-1Sam9:24\">1SA 9:22–9:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:41\">1KI 1:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:49\">1KI 1:49</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth1:8\">EST 1:8</a></p>\n<h2>Receiving guests</h2>\n<h3>Receiving Jesus Christ as a guest</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:7\">LUK 19:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:10\">MAT 9:10</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:15\">MRK 2:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:29\">LUK 5:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:6-Matt26:7\">MAT 26:6–26:7</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:3\">MRK 14:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:1-John12:3\">JHN 12:1–12:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:36\">LUK 7:36</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:49\">LUK 7:49</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:38\">LUK 10:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:1\">LUK 14:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:29\">LUK 24:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:2\">JHN 2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:20\">REV 3:20</a></p>\n<h3>God's people give hospitality</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:32\">ACT 10:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs4:8-2Kgs4:10\">2KI 4:8–4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:11\">MAT 10:11</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark6:10\">MRK 6:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:4\">LUK 9:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:33-Luke10:37\">LUK 10:33–10:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:34\">ACT 16:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:8\">ACT 21:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:7\">ACT 28:7</a></p>\n<h2>Customs associated with receiving guests</h2>\n<h3>Anointing them with oil</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps23:5\">PSA 23:5</a></strong> <em>Anointing with oil was a customary treatment for honoured guests.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps92:10\">PSA 92:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:46\">LUK 7:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:3\">JHN 12:3</a></p>\n<h3>Washing their feet</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:4-Gen18:5\">GEN 18:4–18:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:2\">GEN 19:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:32\">GEN 24:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen43:24\">GEN 43:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam25:41\">1SA 25:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:44\">LUK 7:44</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:1-John13:17\">JHN 13:1–13:17</a> <em>It was usually the slave's duty to wash away dirt accumulated in travelling.</em></p>\n<h3>Guests treated badly</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:20-Judg19:23\">JDG 19:20–19:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam15:11\">2SA 15:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer41:1-Jer41:2\">JER 41:1–41:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:44-Luke7:46\">LUK 7:44–7:46</a></p>\n<h2>Guests rejecting their hosts</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:49\">1KI 1:49</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:15\">JOB 19:15</a></p>\n<h2>Advice given to guests</h2>\n<h3>Do not promote yourself</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:6-Prov25:7\">PRO 25:6–25:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:7-Luke14:11\">LUK 14:7–14:11</a></p>\n<h3>Do not criticise the food</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:27\">1CO 10:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:7\">LUK 10:7</a></p>\n<h3>Do not outstay your welcome</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov25:17\">PRO 25:17</a></p>\n<h2>God invites people to be his guests</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:9\">REV 19:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:1\">ISA 55:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:28\">MAT 11:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:37\">JHN 7:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:17\">REV 22:17</a></p>\n<h3>Some refuse God's invitation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:24\">LUK 14:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:1-Matt22:7\">MAT 22:1–22:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:16-Luke14:20\">LUK 14:16–14:20</a></p>\n<h3>Some accept God's invitation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:8-Matt22:10\">MAT 22:8–22:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:15\">MAT 9:15</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:19\">MRK 2:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:34\">LUK 5:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:21-Luke14:23\">LUK 14:21–14:23</a></p>\n<h2>Guest rooms</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:14\">MRK 14:14</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:18\">MAT 26:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:11\">LUK 22:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phlm1:22\">PHM 1:22</a></p>",
